				"§6★ Integration Quest — Create Mechanical Arm (Ch 2.2) + Ars Nouveau.§r"
				"§fThe §6Enchanting Apparatus§f normally requires you to manually"
				"§fplace reagents on the pedestals around it. §6Create§f fixes that."
				""
				"§eThe Enchanting Apparatus setup (manual):§r"
				"§7• §e1 Enchanting Apparatus§7 center block."
				"§7• §e8 Arcane Pedestals§7 around it (within 3 blocks)."
				"§7• §e1 Arcane Core§7 (or Apprentice/Archmage Core) for the center."
				"§7• §ePlace reagents§7 on the pedestals, §eplace item§7 on the Apparatus,"
				"§7  §eRight-click§7 with a Worn Notebook to start enchanting."
				""
				"§eAutomating with Mechanical Arm:§r"
				"§71. §eMechanical Arm§7 reaches the pedestals from above."
				"§72. §eFilter§7 the Arm to place specific reagent types on specific pedestals."
				"§73. §eA second Arm§7 places the item-to-enchant on the Apparatus center."
				"§74. §eSource Jars§7 adjacent — the Apparatus auto-draws Source when"
				"§7   all reagents are placed (if configured to auto-trigger)."
				"§75. §eArm collects§7 the enchanted item from the output slot."
				""
				"§eHigh-value enchantments to automate:§r"
				"§7• §eFlight (Ars Nouveau)§7 — requires End-tier reagents (Chorus Fruit)."
				"§7• §eSharpness V§7 — requires Dragon Breath (from Ch 3)."
				"§7• §eMending§7 — reagent: Prismarine Shard + Gold."
				"§7• §eUnbreaking III§7 — reagent: Diamond + Obsidian."
				""
				"§a► Set up a Mechanical Arm that feeds reagents to Enchanting Apparatus pedestals."
				"§a► Produce any enchanted item automatically. Mark done."
			]
			dependencies: ["000F0006"]
