			title: "Creative Motor"
			icon: "create:creative_motor"
			description: [
				"§6The Creative Motor§f is a special reward for completing the"
				"§fArs Creo synthesis system. This is not a workhorse power source —"
				"§fit is a §eprecision tool§f for your most demanding single machines."
				""
				"§ePack restriction:§r"
				"§7• §eThis pack caps the Creative Motor at §c256 RPM§7."
				"§7• The default Creative Motor is uncapped (infinite RPM/SU)."
				"§7• §eAt 256 RPM§7 it outputs §e~512 SU§7 — equivalent to a medium-tier"
				"§7  steam boiler setup. Useful, but not game-breaking."
				"§7• This cap exists to preserve the satisfaction of building real power."
				""
				"§eBest uses at 256 RPM:§r"
				"§7• §eGlyph Press§7 — exact RPM doesn't affect glyph quality; any speed works."
				"§7• §eHigh-stress single machine§7 — Mixer needing constant 256-SU draw."
				"§7• §eTest shaft§7 — prototype a Create contraption before building real power."
				"§7• §eArs Creo Source Converter§7 at max legal speed for fastest Source fill."
				""
				"§e⚠ What NOT to use it for:§r"
				"§7• §eDo NOT§7 use it as your primary Brass production line driver."
				"§7  Build a real boiler (Ch 2.5) for that — the cap means it's no faster."
				"§7• §eDo NOT§7 replace your Starbuncle Wheel farm with it."
				"§7  The Wheels are unlimited stacking; the Motor is one machine."
				""
				"§eHow you obtained this:§r"
				"§7• §eNot crafted§7 — it is a quest reward only."
				"§7• §eRecipe removed§7 in KubeJS to enforce the lore: you earn the"
				"§7  Creative Motor by proving you don't need it."
				""
				"§a► The Creative Motor is your reward — claim it below."
			]
			dependencies: ["000F0009"]
		}

